Bauchi State Deputy Governor, Baba Tela, has debunked reports that he resigned his position. Tela made this known in a statement issued by his Press Secretary, Sani Mu’azu Ilelah. He described the viral social media report making the rounds as a figment of the imagination of the author. “For the avoidance of doubt, we would like to assure the peace loving and hard-working people of Bauchi State, in particular and the nation in general, that Sen. Baba Tela has not resigned as the Deputy Governor of Bauchi State. “His Excellency, the deputy Governor, remains committed to the objectives and ideas of the Government of Bauchi State under the able leadership of His Excellency, Sen. Bala Abdulkadir Mohammed, CON (Kauran Bauchi),” the statement said.